{
  "document_id": "job-6",
  "title": "Job 6",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-heading-job-replies:-my-comp",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Job Replies: My Complaint Is Just"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Then Job answered:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“O that my vexation were weighed"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "For then it would be heavier than the sand of the sea;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "For the arrows of the Almighty are in me;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Does the wild ass bray over its grass"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Can that which is tasteless be eaten without salt,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "My appetite refuses to touch them;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "“O that I might have my request"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "that it would please God to crush me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "This would be my consolation;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "What is my strength, that I should wait?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Is my strength the strength of stones,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "In truth I have no help in me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "“Those who withhold kindness from a friend"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "My companions are treacherous like a torrent bed,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "that run dark with ice,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "In time of heat they disappear;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "The caravans turn aside from their course;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "The caravans of Tema look;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "They are disappointed because they were confident;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Such you have now become to me;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Have I said, ‘Make me a gift’?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Or, ‘Save me from an opponent’s hand’?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "“Teach me, and I will be silent;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "How forceful are honest words!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "Do you think that you can reprove words,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "You would even cast lots over the orphan"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "“But now, be pleased to look at me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Turn, I pray; let no wrong be done."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-6-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "Is there any wrong on my tongue?"
    }
  ]
}